Title: 2ZR-FXE (COOLING): WATER PUMP: REMOVAL; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

REMOVAL

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

CAUTION:

  • Support the engine assembly with transaxle until the engine water pump assembly is installed.
  • If the support is removed before the engine water pump assembly is installed, the engine assembly with transaxle may drop.
  • Be careful not to get your hand or fingers pinched when raising or lowering the engine assembly with transaxle.

12. REMOVE ENGINE WATER PUMP ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the bolt, nut and disconnect the 2 cooler brackets of the air conditioner tube and accessory assembly.

(b) Loosen the 5 bolts.

(c) Disconnect the engine water pump assembly connector.

(d) Using a jack and a wooden block, support the engine assembly with transaxle.

*a

Wooden Block

*b

Jack

Wooden Block Placement Location

CAUTION:

  • Support the engine assembly with transaxle until the engine water pump assembly is installed.
  • If the support is removed before the engine water pump assembly is installed, the engine assembly with transaxle may drop.

(e) Remove the nut.

(f) Remove the 2 bolts and separate the engine mounting insulator sub-assembly RH from the engine mounting bracket RH.

(g) Using a jack, slowly lower the engine assembly with transaxle 50 mm (1.97 in.).

CAUTION:

Be careful not to get your hand or fingers pinched when raising or lowering the engine assembly with transaxle.

NOTICE:

  • When raising or lowering the engine assembly with transaxle, be careful of other components.
  • If the engine assembly with transaxle is lowered more than 50 mm (1.97 in.), a hose, wire harness or the engine assembly with transaxle may contact.

*a

50 mm (1.97 in.)

*b

Jack

(h) Apply protective tape to the area shown in the illustration.

Protective Tape

(i) Remove the 5 bolts.

(j) Move the engine water pump assembly to the right side of the vehicle.

Remove in this Direction

Protective Tape

(k) Move the engine water pump assembly toward the bottom of the vehicle until the shaft of the engine water pump assembly is free.

*a

shaft

Remove in this Direction

Protective Tape

(l) Move the engine water pump assembly toward the front of the vehicle and then remove the engine water pump assembly from the top of the vehicle.

Remove in this Direction

Protective Tape

(m) Remove the gasket from the engine water pump assembly.
